{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Job|17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","chapter":17,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":1,"text":"My spirit is broken. My days are extinguished. A graveyard awaits me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":2,"text":"Surely mockers surround me, and my eyes must gaze at their rebellion.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":3,"text":"Accept my pledge! Put up security for me. Who else will be my sponsor?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":4,"text":"You have closed their minds to understanding, therefore you will not honor them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":5,"text":"If a man denounces his friends for a price, the eyes of his children will fail.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":6,"text":"He has made me an object of scorn to the people; I have become a man people spit at.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":7,"text":"My eyes have grown dim from grief, and my whole body has become but a shadow.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":8,"text":"The upright are appalled at this, and the innocent are roused against the godless.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":9,"text":"Yet the righteous person will hold to his way, and the one whose hands are clean will grow stronger.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":10,"text":"But come back and try again, all of you. I will not find a wise man among you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":11,"text":"My days have slipped by; my plans have been ruined, even the things dear to my heart.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":12,"text":"They turned night into day and made light seem near in the face of darkness.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":13,"text":"If I await Sheol as my home, spread out my bed in darkness,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":14,"text":"and say to corruption, “You are my father,” and to the maggot, “My mother” or “My sister,”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:17:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":17,"verse":15,"text":"where then is my hope? Who can see any hope for me?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01: